00:27:36,707 --> 00:27:39,341
Sure you won't be
feeling better
by tonight?

491
00:27:39,407 --> 00:27:43,743
No, no. Let me alone.
Can't you leave me alone?

492
00:27:43,811 --> 00:27:46,845
[Captain andy]
Hello, windy.
What are you doing here?

493
00:27:46,913 --> 00:27:48,946
Just come over
to warn you.

494
00:27:49,014 --> 00:27:51,915
Seen pete
coming along the levee
with the sheriff.

495
00:27:51,983 --> 00:27:53,249
Be along any minute.

496
00:27:53,317 --> 00:27:55,683
Well, let him
come on board.
Our license is paid.

497
00:27:55,752 --> 00:27:58,318
Seems that skunk pete's
up to something.

498
00:27:58,387 --> 00:27:59,819
Seen him yank
a picture of julie

499
00:27:59,887 --> 00:28:01,654
out of a frame
on the levee.

500
00:28:01,722 --> 00:28:02,755
I seen him.

501
00:28:02,822 --> 00:28:04,389
What are we
going to do?

502
00:28:04,457 --> 00:28:07,391
Stay right here.
You know what
i told you.

503
00:28:07,459 --> 00:28:09,626
Steve!
What are you doing
with that knife?

504
00:28:09,693 --> 00:28:11,760
I'm not going to
hurt her, you fool.

505
00:28:11,828 --> 00:28:14,262
Leave me be.
I know what i'm doing.

506
00:28:14,330 --> 00:28:16,463
It won't
hurt much, darling.

507
00:28:17,331 --> 00:28:18,264
Aah!

508
00:28:18,332 --> 00:28:20,199
Steve!

509
00:28:47,249 --> 00:28:49,050
Hello,
windy.

510
00:28:49,118 --> 00:28:50,184
Captain
hawks,

511
00:28:50,251 --> 00:28:51,518
do you
acknowledge

512
00:28:51,586 --> 00:28:53,586
to be owner of
the show boat?

513
00:28:53,654 --> 00:28:55,720
Why, of course i do.

514
00:28:55,788 --> 00:28:56,955
What do you want?

515
00:28:57,023 --> 00:28:58,422
I have
an unpleasant duty.

516
00:28:58,490 --> 00:29:01,457
I understand that you
have a miscegenation
case on board.

517
00:29:01,525 --> 00:29:02,457
What's that?

518
00:29:02,526 --> 00:29:03,692
[Captain andy]
How's that?

519
00:29:03,760 --> 00:29:05,926
A case of a negro woman
married to a white man...

520
00:29:05,994 --> 00:29:07,927
a criminal offense
in this state.

521
00:29:07,995 --> 00:29:10,597
No. No such thing
on board this boat.

522
00:29:10,664 --> 00:29:13,798
The name
of the white man
is steve baker.

523
00:29:15,134 --> 00:29:17,100
The name
of the negress...

524
00:29:17,168 --> 00:29:19,869
the name
of the negress
is julie dosher.

525
00:29:19,936 --> 00:29:21,370
Which one's
them?

526
00:29:21,437 --> 00:29:25,339
I am steve baker.
This is my wife.

527
00:29:27,241 --> 00:29:29,508
Julie dosher,
my information says

528
00:29:29,575 --> 00:29:31,510
you were born
in mississippi.

529
00:29:31,576 --> 00:29:34,077
Your pop was white,
your mammy black.

530
00:29:34,146 --> 00:29:35,545
Is that right?

531
00:29:35,613 --> 00:29:37,212
Yes, that's right.

532
00:29:37,281 --> 00:29:39,248
You two better
get your things

533
00:29:39,315 --> 00:29:40,815
and come along
with me.

534
00:29:40,882 --> 00:29:43,483
You wouldn't
call a man a white man

535
00:29:43,550 --> 00:29:45,284
that had negro blood
in him, would you?

536
00:29:45,352 --> 00:29:47,285
No, i wouldn't,
not in mississippi.

537
00:29:47,353 --> 00:29:48,920
One drop
of negro blood

538
00:29:48,987 --> 00:29:50,921
makes you a negro
in these parts.

539
00:29:50,989 --> 00:29:54,756
Well, i got more than a drop
of negro blood in me,

540
00:29:54,825 --> 00:29:56,457
and that's a fact.

541
00:29:57,959 --> 00:29:59,493
Are you ready
to swear that

542
00:29:59,561 --> 00:30:00,960
in a court of law?

543
00:30:01,028 --> 00:30:02,728
I'll swear to it
anyplace.

544
00:30:02,797 --> 00:30:04,596
I'll do more
than that.

545
00:30:04,663 --> 00:30:06,998
Look at all
these folks here.

546
00:30:07,066 --> 00:30:08,498
Every one of them
can swear

547
00:30:08,567 --> 00:30:10,766
that i got negro blood
in me this minute.

548
00:30:10,834 --> 00:30:13,069
That's how white i am.

549
00:30:14,236 --> 00:30:17,004
Well, i've seen
fairer men than you

550
00:30:17,072 --> 00:30:18,472
that were negroes.

551
00:30:18,539 --> 00:30:20,605
Still,
you better tell that
to the judge.

552
00:30:20,674 --> 00:30:24,508
Ahem! Ike vallon,
you've known me

553
00:30:24,576 --> 00:30:26,509
the better part
of 25 years.

554
00:30:26,577 --> 00:30:29,478
I was keelboating
when you was running barefoot

555
00:30:29,546 --> 00:30:31,013
around the landing.

556
00:30:31,080 --> 00:30:34,848
Now, i'm telling you...
me, windy mcclain...

557
00:30:34,916 --> 00:30:37,350
that white man's
got negro blood in him.

558
00:30:37,417 --> 00:30:38,784
But this fellow
told me...

559
00:30:38,851 --> 00:30:41,018
i don't care
what anybody told you.

560
00:30:41,087 --> 00:30:43,520
I'm taking my oath
on what i just said.

561
00:30:43,588 --> 00:30:45,788
Steve's got
negro blood in him.

562
00:30:47,091 --> 00:30:49,890
Do you all stand by
what windy just said?

563
00:30:49,958 --> 00:30:51,291
Of course we do.

564
00:30:53,027 --> 00:30:55,461
You look like
a respectable woman.

565
00:30:55,529 --> 00:30:56,928
I am.

566
00:30:56,996 --> 00:30:59,963
Windy wouldn't tell a lie
to save his own life.

567
00:31:00,032 --> 00:31:01,231
You know that, sheriff.

568
00:31:01,299 --> 00:31:02,498
Yes, i know.

569
00:31:02,567 --> 00:31:05,233
I reckon i'll have to take
windy's word for it,

570
00:31:05,301 --> 00:31:07,434
but from now on,
it's your business and not mine.

571
00:31:07,503 --> 00:31:08,535
I warn you...

572
00:31:08,603 --> 00:31:10,470
if these folks around here
ever got wind

573
00:31:10,537 --> 00:31:12,738
that you've got negroes
acting with whites,

574
00:31:12,806 --> 00:31:14,740
they'll ride you
out of town

575
00:31:14,806 --> 00:31:17,441
on something that won't
set so easy as a boat.

576
00:31:17,509 --> 00:31:19,142
Get away from that window!

577
00:31:19,210 --> 00:31:21,843
Go on about your business.
Break it up!

578
00:31:26,547 --> 00:31:28,481
Now you go!
Both of you!

579
00:31:28,548 --> 00:31:30,982
You needn't look at us
like that.

580
00:31:31,051 --> 00:31:32,984
We're not going to
hurt you.

581
00:31:33,051 --> 00:31:36,219
We're going right away.
Come on, honey.

582
00:31:39,555 --> 00:31:41,489
Julie! Julie!

583
00:31:41,557 --> 00:31:42,990
Nola, where are
you going?

584
00:31:43,058 --> 00:31:44,491
I'm going to julie!

585
00:31:44,559 --> 00:31:45,991
Come back here
this instant.

586
00:31:46,060 --> 00:31:47,493
No daughter of mine
will talk to that...

587
00:31:47,560 --> 00:31:49,027
let me go, mother!

588
00:31:54,031 --> 00:31:57,866
I think my show boat's
made a darn fine gal
out of my daughter.

589
00:31:57,933 --> 00:32:00,534
But where
do we go from here?
Hanged if i know.

590
00:32:00,602 --> 00:32:03,269
We can't give
no more shows
without a leading man.

591
00:32:03,337 --> 00:32:05,036
Or a leading lady.

592
00:32:05,105 --> 00:32:06,971
I can play
the lead, can't i?

593
00:32:07,039 --> 00:32:08,472
No. You're
a comedienne.

594
00:32:08,540 --> 00:32:11,241
I was thinking
maybe we'd let
noli jump in.

595
00:32:11,308 --> 00:32:12,741
She knows
all the parts.

596
00:32:12,809 --> 00:32:13,942
Over my dead body.

597
00:32:14,009 --> 00:32:15,977
There never was
an actress in my family,

598
00:32:16,044 --> 00:32:17,311
and there ain't
going to be.

599
00:32:17,378 --> 00:32:21,080
Now if only there
was anybody to play
steve's part.

600
00:32:21,149 --> 00:32:22,748
What about frank?

601
00:32:22,815 --> 00:32:24,082
[Parthy]
Hmm!

602
00:32:24,150 --> 00:32:25,750
Fine leading man
he'd make

603
00:32:25,817 --> 00:32:27,283
with that face
and those flat feet.

604
00:32:27,352 --> 00:32:29,285
I never asked
to play leads, did i?

605
00:32:29,352 --> 00:32:31,920
I never set up
to be a beauty.

606
00:32:31,988 --> 00:32:33,421
Just a minute,
captain!

607
00:32:33,489 --> 00:32:35,289
Mercy! Something
must be on fire,

608
00:32:35,356 --> 00:32:36,523
the way
queenie's running.

609
00:32:36,590 --> 00:32:37,790
Now what's
the trouble,
queenie?

610
00:32:37,858 --> 00:32:39,992
There's a powerful
fine-looking fellow out here.

611
00:32:40,059 --> 00:32:42,026
Wants to know if you-all
could accommodate him

612
00:32:42,094 --> 00:32:44,127
by taking him down the river
far as the next town.

613
00:32:44,195 --> 00:32:45,228
We don't carry
no passengers...

614
00:32:45,296 --> 00:32:46,695
fine-looking,
did you say?

615
00:32:46,764 --> 00:32:47,997
Is he an actor?

616
00:32:48,063 --> 00:32:51,932
Might be, but he seems more
like the kind of a gentleman

617
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:53,933
it's a pleasure to wait on.

618
00:32:54,002 --> 00:32:55,601
There he is.

619
00:32:55,668 --> 00:32:56,935
I thought, sir,
if i could have

620
00:32:57,003 --> 00:32:58,970
a bed on your boat
tonight,

621
00:32:59,037 --> 00:33:01,538
i could pay my way
as far as fort adams.

622
00:33:01,606 --> 00:33:02,806
You ain't
an actor,
are you?

623
00:33:02,873 --> 00:33:04,973
An actor, sir?
No, captain.

624
00:33:05,041 --> 00:33:08,475
I'm a ravenal.
Gaylord ravenal is my name,

625
00:33:08,544 --> 00:33:10,644
of the tennessee ravenals.

626
00:33:10,711 --> 00:33:13,112
I knew it. He looked
like an aristocrat to me.

627
00:33:13,180 --> 00:33:16,214
Aristocrat? Huh!
Looks more like
a river gambler.

628
00:33:16,282 --> 00:33:18,215
Well, i'm going to
take a chance.

629
00:33:18,283 --> 00:33:19,750
Look here, sir.

630
00:33:19,817 --> 00:33:22,484
I'm looking for a juvenile
leading man.

631
00:33:22,552 --> 00:33:25,186
Am i to understand
you're offering me
the position, sir?

632
00:33:25,253 --> 00:33:28,021
Andy hawks will wind up
in a lunatic asylum yet.

633
00:33:28,088 --> 00:33:30,756
If you can
play the parts
to my satisfaction,

634
00:33:30,825 --> 00:33:32,758
i'll give you
$15 a week

635
00:33:32,825 --> 00:33:34,492
and a chance
to see the world.

636
00:33:34,559 --> 00:33:35,793
I've seen it.

637
00:33:35,860 --> 00:33:37,993
We don't usually pick up actors
off the wharves,

638
00:33:38,061 --> 00:33:39,829
but we can't be choosy
just now.

639
00:33:39,896 --> 00:33:43,498
Madam, your courtesy
is only exceeded
by your charm.

640
00:33:43,565 --> 00:33:45,199
Ha ha ha!

641
00:33:45,265 --> 00:33:46,499
Mother! Father!

642
00:33:46,567 --> 00:33:48,500
Don't let them go,
please, papa!

643
00:33:48,568 --> 00:33:50,935
Don't send julie and steve
away like this.

644
00:33:51,003 --> 00:33:52,937
Nobody will know about them
in the next town.

645
00:33:53,003 --> 00:33:54,537
Julie's my friend.

646
00:33:54,605 --> 00:33:56,206
That's a nice thing
to say.

647
00:33:56,272 --> 00:33:58,206
Well, she is! She is!

648
00:33:58,274 --> 00:33:59,941
She's been my friend ever since
she's been on this boat,

649
00:34:00,008 --> 00:34:01,708
and if you're going to
send her away

650
00:34:01,776 --> 00:34:03,443
for something she can't help,
i'll go, too!

651
00:34:03,510 --> 00:34:04,443
Nola!

652
00:34:04,511 --> 00:34:05,944
Nola, don't talk nonsense.

653
00:34:06,012 --> 00:34:07,445
You've got to stay here
with your mother,

654
00:34:07,513 --> 00:34:08,946
no matter what.

655
00:34:09,014 --> 00:34:10,948
And another thing...
i'm depending on you

656
00:34:11,014 --> 00:34:13,382
to play the leads
till we can get somebody.

657
00:34:13,450 --> 00:34:15,183
See, nola?
What a chance for you.

658
00:34:15,251 --> 00:34:16,751
I just know
you can act.

659
00:34:16,818 --> 00:34:18,519
And if this young man
wants to play the leads

660
00:34:18,587 --> 00:34:19,819
and play opposite you,

661
00:34:19,887 --> 00:34:22,654
i can get you both ready
by tomorrow night.

662
00:34:22,722 --> 00:34:24,655
Are you a quick study?

663
00:34:24,724 --> 00:34:25,923
Lightning.

664
00:34:25,991 --> 00:34:27,492
[Steve]
Ready, julie?

665
00:34:27,558 --> 00:34:29,492
I didn't have time
to get everything
together, captain.

666
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:30,960
If you'll bundle up
our trash

667
00:34:31,027 --> 00:34:33,461
and leave it
at the post office
in new orleans,

668
00:34:33,529 --> 00:34:34,963
we'll pick it up.

669
00:34:35,029 --> 00:34:36,963
Do you need
any money, steve?

670
00:34:37,031 --> 00:34:39,465
No. I guess we'll
make out all right.

671
00:34:39,533 --> 00:34:40,966
Thanks. Good-bye.

672
00:34:41,033 --> 00:34:42,467
Good-bye, steve.

673
00:34:42,534 --> 00:34:44,368
Forget it.

674
00:34:44,436 --> 00:34:45,969
Good-bye, nola.

675
00:34:47,137 --> 00:34:52,607
I'll write to you,
and you write to me,

676
00:35:02,013 --> 00:35:03,947
julie! Julie!

677
00:35:04,014 --> 00:35:06,147
Don't look back,
darling.

678
00:35:09,951 --> 00:35:12,418
Bye, master steve.

679
00:35:12,486 --> 00:35:15,187
Good-bye, miss julie.

680
00:35:15,255 --> 00:35:16,687
Bye, joe.

681
00:35:16,756 --> 00:35:18,154
Good-bye, joe.

682
00:35:21,025 --> 00:35:22,292
Good-bye.

683
00:35:42,372 --> 00:35:43,938
We ain't got much time.

684
00:35:44,005 --> 00:35:46,439
Mr. Ravenal, i want to see
how you handle dialogue.

685
00:35:46,507 --> 00:35:48,474
Will you read
that speech right there?

686
00:35:48,542 --> 00:35:50,408
Now, the idea
of this character is

687
00:35:50,476 --> 00:35:51,910
you're in love with her.

688
00:35:51,976 --> 00:35:53,911
Now, come on.
Just a sample.

689
00:35:53,978 --> 00:35:55,379
What do i do,
papa?

690
00:35:55,445 --> 00:35:56,913
Oh, you just smile.
That'll get them.

691
00:35:56,980 --> 00:35:58,313
Miss lucy,
will you be mine?

692
00:35:58,381 --> 00:36:00,115
Hmm!

693
00:36:00,181 --> 00:36:01,882
Ha ha ha! Gosh, no.
Nothing like it.

694
00:36:01,950 --> 00:36:04,417
More feeling.
More like you meant it.

695
00:36:04,485 --> 00:36:06,885
You love her. Gosh almighty,
man, you love her!

696
00:36:06,953 --> 00:36:08,619
Go on and tell her.

697
00:36:08,688 --> 00:36:10,388
Oh, i understand.

698
00:36:11,989 --> 00:36:14,823
Miss lucy,
will you be mine?

699
00:36:19,794 --> 00:36:22,662
Ha ha ha!

700
00:36:34,504 --> 00:36:35,636
[Applause]

701
00:36:57,451 --> 00:36:58,650
Did you like it,
mrs. Ewing?

702
00:36:58,718 --> 00:37:00,151
I've seen it
four times.

703
00:37:00,219 --> 00:37:01,419
I liked it
better than ever.

704
00:37:01,486 --> 00:37:03,420
Don't you think
the leading man
is gorgeous?

705
00:37:03,488 --> 00:37:05,422
Yes. He took his part
off quite good.

706
00:37:05,488 --> 00:37:07,689
I liked the leading lady
the best, though.

707
00:37:07,757 --> 00:37:09,891
Did you understand the moral
of the play, my dear?

708
00:37:09,959 --> 00:37:12,426
Oh, sure, mom.
Did you see
how he kissed her?

709
00:37:12,493 --> 00:37:15,393
Yes. I hardly thought
that was in the best of taste.

710
00:37:15,462 --> 00:37:17,429
Well, that's
show business.

711
00:37:17,496 --> 00:37:18,896
What's show business?

712
00:37:18,964 --> 00:37:22,098
I've been trouping
up and down this river
for 12 years.

713
00:37:22,166 --> 00:37:23,599
Nobody ever heard of me.

714
00:37:23,667 --> 00:37:25,934
This ravenal has been
acting exactly three weeks.

715
00:37:26,001 --> 00:37:27,935
They make a star
out of him.

716
00:37:28,003 --> 00:37:29,936
I feel the same way,
frank.

717
00:37:30,004 --> 00:37:31,371
Look at magnolia.

718
00:37:31,438 --> 00:37:33,939
Her picture with ravenal
is on all the posters.

719
00:37:34,006 --> 00:37:35,706
We're not in town
an hour

720
00:37:35,774 --> 00:37:37,941
before captain andy
has their faces
on every ashcan.

721
00:37:38,009 --> 00:37:39,943
You want to know the secret
of their quick success?

722
00:37:40,010 --> 00:37:41,911
They're falling in love
with each other.

723
00:37:41,978 --> 00:37:43,345
What's that got
to do with it?

724
00:37:43,412 --> 00:37:45,946
Well, they make love
on the stage,
and it rings true.

725
00:37:46,014 --> 00:37:47,280
That's why they're a hit.

726
00:37:47,348 --> 00:37:49,448
Well, i've been
playing opposite you
for five years,

727
00:37:49,516 --> 00:37:50,849
and i love you.

728
00:37:50,917 --> 00:37:53,451
Yeah, but maybe
i don't love you.

729
00:37:53,518 --> 00:37:55,885
So you're responsible
for our failure!

730
00:37:55,953 --> 00:37:58,387
We'll never be stars
on this show boat.

731
00:37:58,455 --> 00:38:01,389
You talk
as if you expected
to live on this barge

732
00:38:01,457 --> 00:38:02,890
the rest
of your life.

733
00:38:02,957 --> 00:38:04,890
Ain't you got
no ambition?

734
00:38:04,959 --> 00:38:07,892
Sure,
i got ambition.
I want to marry you.

735
00:38:07,961 --> 00:38:10,894
You know our rules,
mr. Schultz.

736
00:38:10,962 --> 00:38:12,895
No gentleman
allowed in no lady's
dressing room.

737
00:38:12,963 --> 00:38:14,397
He was only waiting
while l...

738
