¶ no matter what you say,
i thinks you do ¶

1310
01:08:19,606 --> 01:08:22,040
queenie? Queenie!

1311
01:08:22,108 --> 01:08:24,042
Mrs. Hawks wants you
to bring some hot water

1312
01:08:24,109 --> 01:08:25,509
up to miss nola's room.

1313
01:08:25,576 --> 01:08:26,843
My goodness!

1314
01:08:26,911 --> 01:08:28,177
You and me
and mrs. Hawks

1315
01:08:28,245 --> 01:08:29,511
will have to do
all we can.

1316
01:08:29,580 --> 01:08:31,712
There's no way
to get a doctor
tonight.

1317
01:08:31,781 --> 01:08:33,047
I'll get a doctor.

1318
01:08:33,115 --> 01:08:35,582
You'll get a doctor?

1319
01:08:35,649 --> 01:08:37,317
Well, i've never
seen joe

1320
01:08:37,383 --> 01:08:39,317
move that fast before.

1321
01:08:40,953 --> 01:08:44,153
Where's gay?
Where's my gay?

1322
01:08:44,222 --> 01:08:46,454
Suppose
he's drowned?

1323
01:08:46,523 --> 01:08:48,289
He ain't drowned.

1324
01:08:50,024 --> 01:08:51,325
Gay and frank
probably

1325
01:08:51,392 --> 01:08:53,226
couldn't get back
to the boat.

1326
01:08:53,293 --> 01:08:54,993
Most likely,
they're staying
at a hotel

1327
01:08:55,062 --> 01:08:56,594
till the morning.

1328
01:08:56,662 --> 01:08:58,629
And his baby
being born.

1329
01:08:58,697 --> 01:09:00,997
Gay didn't know it.

1330
01:09:01,065 --> 01:09:03,298
We didn't
think that...

1331
01:09:03,366 --> 01:09:05,467
it's much sooner.

1332
01:09:05,534 --> 01:09:07,234
How could gay
know it?

1333
01:09:07,302 --> 01:09:10,270
Of course he couldn't.
Now, now, don't get
excited, deary.

1334
01:09:10,337 --> 01:09:13,571
Oh, lie back.
That's a girl.

1335
01:09:14,807 --> 01:09:15,806
Three jacks.

1336
01:09:15,874 --> 01:09:17,307
He wins again.

1337
01:09:17,374 --> 01:09:19,575
Beats 10s
and 2s.

1338
01:09:19,643 --> 01:09:21,309
By george,
it's 2:30.

1339
01:09:21,378 --> 01:09:22,310
Aw, come on.

1340
01:09:22,378 --> 01:09:24,345
You've got
nothing else
to do.

1341
01:09:24,412 --> 01:09:27,280
No. I'm
clean out.

1342
01:09:27,348 --> 01:09:28,982
Cut.

1343
01:09:29,048 --> 01:09:31,517
[Snoring]

1344
01:09:31,583 --> 01:09:34,017
[Thunder]

1345
01:09:45,992 --> 01:09:48,393
Captain andy!
Any news?

1346
01:09:48,461 --> 01:09:50,060
Not yet.

1347
01:09:54,664 --> 01:09:57,165
¶ keep on
goin' ¶

1348
01:09:57,233 --> 01:10:00,134
¶ don't let
that river ¶

1349
01:10:00,201 --> 01:10:02,669
¶ get the better
of you ¶

1350
01:10:02,736 --> 01:10:04,870
¶ come on,
you, joe ¶

1351
01:10:04,937 --> 01:10:10,940
¶ come on,
you good old joe ¶

1352
01:10:11,009 --> 01:10:12,708
fine time to sing.

1353
01:10:12,775 --> 01:10:14,942
Dragging me out of bed
in the middle of the night,

1354
01:10:15,011 --> 01:10:16,977
telling me the river
had calmed down.

1355
01:10:17,045 --> 01:10:18,545
Lying son of satan.

1356
01:10:18,613 --> 01:10:22,381
¶ no matter
what you say ¶

1357
01:10:22,447 --> 01:10:28,652
¶ ah still
suits me ¶

1358
01:10:29,986 --> 01:10:31,152
cootchy cootchy
cootchy.

1359
01:10:31,220 --> 01:10:32,586
Hee hee hee!

1360
01:10:32,655 --> 01:10:34,154
Cootchy
cootchy cootchy!

1361
01:10:34,222 --> 01:10:35,488
Go away, hawks.

1362
01:10:35,557 --> 01:10:37,156
You're making
a nuisance
of yourself.

1363
01:10:37,224 --> 01:10:38,891
I got an idea
what to call her.

1364
01:10:38,958 --> 01:10:40,125
I don't care
to hear it.

1365
01:10:40,193 --> 01:10:41,193
Kim.

1366
01:10:41,259 --> 01:10:43,593
Kim? That ain't
no name.

1367
01:10:43,662 --> 01:10:45,061
I made it up.

1368
01:10:45,129 --> 01:10:47,796
"K" for kentucky,
"l" for illinois,
and "m" for missouri,

1369
01:10:47,864 --> 01:10:50,765
since she was
born on the river
inside three states.

1370
01:10:50,832 --> 01:10:52,599
Humph. Kim!

1371
01:10:52,668 --> 01:10:54,234
[Fussing]

1372
01:10:55,268 --> 01:10:57,503
Cootchy cootchy
cootchy cootchy!

1373
01:11:04,741 --> 01:11:07,309
Hello. You're up early,
mrs. Hawks.

1374
01:11:08,577 --> 01:11:09,876
Good morning,
madam.

1375
01:11:09,945 --> 01:11:11,444
I knew
this was coming.

1376
01:11:11,512 --> 01:11:13,712
I knew from the first minute
i set eyes on you

1377
01:11:13,780 --> 01:11:15,380
that you was the kind
to bring trouble

1378
01:11:15,447 --> 01:11:16,848
to them that
loved you.

1379
01:11:16,914 --> 01:11:19,616
I knew you'd go carousing
the first chance you got

1380
01:11:19,683 --> 01:11:21,283
and break
my girl's heart,

1381
01:11:21,351 --> 01:11:22,817
and i wish
the lord had kept you

1382
01:11:22,886 --> 01:11:24,319
from ever setting foot
on this boat.

1383
01:11:24,386 --> 01:11:26,653
Indeed? Then you'll
be glad to know

1384
01:11:26,721 --> 01:11:28,154
that i'm leaving it
forever,

1385
01:11:28,222 --> 01:11:29,955
and i'm taking
my wife with me.

1386
01:11:30,023 --> 01:11:31,723
Humph. When?

1387
01:11:31,791 --> 01:11:33,524
The minute the river
goes down enough

1388
01:11:33,592 --> 01:11:35,559
for us to take
our things ashore.

1389
01:11:35,626 --> 01:11:37,961
You will not go today,
gaylord ravenal.

1390
01:11:38,027 --> 01:11:40,262
Why not?
What have you to say
about it, anyway?

1391
01:11:40,329 --> 01:11:41,896
She'll not
leave her home

1392
01:11:41,964 --> 01:11:44,030
till you've money
to care for her proper,

1393
01:11:44,098 --> 01:11:46,699
and you know how long
before that will be.

1394
01:11:46,767 --> 01:11:48,199
And suppose
i was to tell you

1395
01:11:48,268 --> 01:11:50,468
that i had money,
and plenty of it?

1396
01:11:50,536 --> 01:11:52,803
I still say
you can't take a girl

1397
01:11:52,871 --> 01:11:55,404
that's been laying
close to death all night

1398
01:11:55,472 --> 01:11:58,540
and a 5-hour baby
off this boat today.

1399
01:11:58,608 --> 01:12:00,140
A baby?

1400
01:12:00,208 --> 01:12:01,976
A baby!

1401
01:12:05,012 --> 01:12:07,445
Nola.

1402
01:12:07,512 --> 01:12:08,446
Nola.

1403
01:12:08,513 --> 01:12:10,347
Shh!

1404
01:12:10,414 --> 01:12:14,148
Gay! We surprised you.

1405
01:12:14,217 --> 01:12:17,352
Who? Who
surprised me? You?

1406
01:12:17,418 --> 01:12:19,887
No. She did.

1407
01:12:26,491 --> 01:12:27,591
She's sleeping.

1408
01:12:27,658 --> 01:12:30,292
That's what her mother
should be doing.

1409
01:12:30,361 --> 01:12:32,760
Try to sleep, darling.

1410
01:12:37,031 --> 01:12:38,597
Humph.

1411
01:12:41,634 --> 01:12:44,201
Cootchy cootchy...

1412
01:12:47,137 --> 01:12:48,838
now, i want you
to get well quickly

1413
01:12:48,905 --> 01:12:50,838
so i can take you
to chicago with me,

1414
01:12:50,907 --> 01:12:52,873
just we three together.

1415
01:12:52,941 --> 01:12:55,041
You'd like that,
wouldn't you?

1416
01:13:04,381 --> 01:13:05,781
Good morning.

1417
01:13:09,651 --> 01:13:11,751
Darling, is my hat
on straight?

1418
01:13:11,819 --> 01:13:13,486
You look enchanting.

1419
01:13:14,620 --> 01:13:16,288
[Shouting]

1420
01:13:26,061 --> 01:13:28,428
Ha ha ha!

1421
01:13:28,496 --> 01:13:30,329
Gay, you're
wonderful.

1422
01:13:33,101 --> 01:13:34,602
Gay just
can't lose.

1423
01:13:34,670 --> 01:13:36,571
What's good
in the next race?

1424
01:13:51,017 --> 01:13:51,951
[Honk honk]

1425
01:13:52,018 --> 01:13:53,751
[Bang]

1426
01:13:58,224 --> 01:13:59,858
[Honk honk]

1427
01:14:01,226 --> 01:14:03,594
Ha ha ha!

1428
01:14:03,661 --> 01:14:05,996
There isn't anything
i haven't got...

1429
01:14:06,064 --> 01:14:07,664
nothing left
to wish for.

1430
01:14:07,732 --> 01:14:09,799
We've been through
some pretty hard times.

1431
01:14:09,867 --> 01:14:12,268
Might just as well
enjoy the good times.

1432
01:14:12,336 --> 01:14:14,504
[Bang]

1433
01:14:14,571 --> 01:14:16,471
Something must
be wrong, darling.

1434
01:14:16,539 --> 01:14:18,173
Ha ha ha!

1435
01:14:19,542 --> 01:14:21,243
"We may move
to a large apartment.

1436
01:14:21,310 --> 01:14:24,011
We need more room,"
and so and so and so.

1437
01:14:24,079 --> 01:14:25,412
What was all that?

1438
01:14:25,480 --> 01:14:27,681
Nothing. Just that
they don't like it

1439
01:14:27,749 --> 01:14:29,350
at the palmer house
anymore.

1440
01:14:29,417 --> 01:14:31,352
Ain't you going to
read it to me?

1441
01:14:31,419 --> 01:14:34,988
Oh, yes.
"We're placing kim
in a convent school."

1442
01:14:35,055 --> 01:14:37,757
It will
cost them a fortune.
Why did they do that?

1443
01:14:37,825 --> 01:14:40,259
"Gay thinks kim
will have a chance

1444
01:14:40,326 --> 01:14:42,394
to form better
social connections."

1445
01:14:42,462 --> 01:14:45,130
Public school is the best,
but not for gay and nola.

1446
01:14:45,198 --> 01:14:47,498
Nothing's any good for them
unless it costs a lot.

1447
01:14:47,566 --> 01:14:51,202
Did he buy her any
new diamond bracelets
or automobiles?

1448
01:14:51,270 --> 01:14:52,703
She don't say.

1449
01:14:52,771 --> 01:14:54,038
Well, what
does she say?

1450
01:14:54,106 --> 01:14:55,805
"I hope
you and mother
are well,"

1451
01:14:55,873 --> 01:14:57,440
and so and so
and so.

1452
01:14:57,508 --> 01:14:59,142
"Give my regards
to joe and queenie,

1453
01:14:59,210 --> 01:15:01,811
and don't forget"...
so and so and so.

1454
01:15:01,879 --> 01:15:03,612
"Hasn't the weather
been fine?"

1455
01:15:03,680 --> 01:15:05,614
So and so
and so and so.

1456
01:15:05,682 --> 01:15:07,249
"Your loving
daughter, noli."

1457
01:15:07,317 --> 01:15:08,851
Very inter

1458
01:15:08,919 --> 01:15:10,619
you know what i'd
like to do, parthy?

1459
01:15:10,687 --> 01:15:11,819
No.

1460
01:15:11,887 --> 01:15:13,721
After we put up
the show boat
for the winter,

1461
01:15:13,789 --> 01:15:16,090
how about you and me
making a trip
up there?

1462
01:15:16,158 --> 01:15:18,393
Chicago?
You must be crazy.

1463
01:15:18,460 --> 01:15:20,227
Well, i've got
a kind of a feeling

1464
01:15:20,295 --> 01:15:22,429
i'd like to see
noli and gay.

1465
01:15:22,497 --> 01:15:25,766
I don't care
to see gay again
as long as i live.

1466
01:15:25,833 --> 01:15:27,433
He's a wastrel,
an adventurer,

1467
01:15:27,501 --> 01:15:29,969
a cheap river gambler
with a high and mighty air,

1468
01:15:30,037 --> 01:15:31,304
and mark my words...

1469
01:15:31,371 --> 01:15:32,305
shh shh shh!

1470
01:15:32,372 --> 01:15:34,739
We ain't seen kim
in a long while.

1471
01:15:34,807 --> 01:15:36,641
She must be getting
kind of big.

1472
01:15:36,709 --> 01:15:38,977
Smart as a whip,
too, i guess.

1473
01:15:39,045 --> 01:15:42,780
Did i show you
those crayon pictures
she sent me last week?

1474
01:15:42,847 --> 01:15:45,282
Teddy roosevelt
and the one
of the battleship?

1475
01:15:45,350 --> 01:15:47,084
Hee hee hee!
I seen them.

1476
01:15:47,152 --> 01:15:48,752
Oh, she's smart,
all right.

1477
01:15:48,820 --> 01:15:49,820
Yes.

1478
01:15:49,888 --> 01:15:51,521
Come on.
Let's you and me
make the trip.

1479
01:15:51,589 --> 01:15:55,558
You can bake a cake
and bring it to her
up to the school.

1480
01:15:55,626 --> 01:15:56,993
Huh?

1481
01:15:57,961 --> 01:16:00,262
Well... maybe.

1482
01:16:03,933 --> 01:16:06,300
You won't find
another room like this
at the price.

1483
01:16:06,368 --> 01:16:09,470
Well, anyway,
it's chicago, kiddo.

1484
01:16:09,538 --> 01:16:11,472
Looks like somebody's
living in it.

1485
01:16:11,540 --> 01:16:13,907
Well, they won't be
after this morning.

1486
01:16:13,975 --> 01:16:16,509
12 solid weeks
gone by

1487
01:16:16,577 --> 01:16:18,612
and not
a penny paid.

1488
01:16:18,679 --> 01:16:22,181
No, ma'am,
i have me own bills.

1489
01:16:26,252 --> 01:16:28,387
Is that you,
nola?

1490
01:16:28,455 --> 01:16:30,388
Elly.

1491
